• Nile River flows North from central Africa to the Mediterranean sea.
Egyptians believed Osiris brought civilization to Egypt.
Egyptian pyramids were built primarily during the time of the Old Kingdom (2700 to 2200 BCE) Pyramids were part of large building complexes dedicated to the dead, in effect a city of the dead.
